id: hac-9hs1
title: Auto Release blocker issue lookup split a quoted search query
description: "The first production auto-release published v2026.7.21 successfully, then the parent workflow failed while searching for a stale blocker issue because escaped quotes were passed literally to gh."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: automation,github-actions,production-follow-up,release
created_at: "2026-07-21T18:17:11.729Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T18:26:33.422Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-21T18:18:08.973Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: Both blocker issue lookups pass the complete title search as one argument; a production same-day release completes the parent workflow
goal: lossless-automatic-releases
objective: conditional-release-orchestration
value: Keep successful scheduled releases green and make blocker issue maintenance reliable.
impact: Prevents false failed runs after successful publication.
outcome: The parent Auto Release workflow completes after the tag publisher succeeds.
why_now: Production run 29855651273 exposed the post-publication failure.
parent: hac-wwsi
reviewer: unbraind
risk: high
confidence: 100
sprint: release-automation
release: 2026.7.21-2
reporter: codex-root
severity: medium
environment: GitHub Actions Auto Release workflow
repro_steps: "Publish a release, then execute the stale scheduled release blocker cleanup step."
resolution: Introduced an explicit search_query variable and passed it as one quoted argument in both stale-blocker cleanup and scheduled-failure reporting.
expected_result: Both blocker lookup paths accept the complete title query and the parent workflow can finish after publication.
actual_result: "Auto Release run 29856833835 completed every step, Release run 29856953305 published v2026.7.21-2, and independent exact-version checks passed through npm, npx, Bun, and bunx."
affected_version: 2026.7.21
fixed_version: 2026.7.21-2
component: release-automation
regression: false
customer_impact: No package outage; the successfully published release was reported as a failed parent workflow.
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T18:17:11.729Z",codex-root,"Production evidence is public: Auto Release run 29855651273 reached successful tag publication, then failed only in stale-blocker cleanup; tag-driven Release run 29855763180 succeeded."
  "2026-07-21T18:26:33.400Z",codex-root,"Final public production proof: Auto Release https://github.com/unbraind/homeassistant-cli/actions/runs/29856833835 succeeded, including tag publication wait and stale-blocker cleanup; tag-driven Release https://github.com/unbraind/homeassistant-cli/actions/runs/29856953305 succeeded; GitHub release https://github.com/unbraind/homeassistant-cli/releases/tag/v2026.7.21-2 is published."
  "2026-07-21T18:26:33.400Z",codex-root,"Independent registry proof returned version 2026.7.21-2 and exact execution succeeded via npm install plus npx and Bun add plus bunx. The v2026.7.21-2 tag contains matching package.json and Commander CLI versions, and no scheduled-release blocker issue remains open."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T18:17:11.729Z",codex-root,The release guard correctly rejected an empty 2026.7.21-2 section until this distinct production fix had explicit release lineage.
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-21T18:17:11.729Z",codex-root,A post-publication maintenance step can make the parent run red even when the artifact is healthy; it must be tested as part of end-to-end release proof.
files[1]{path,scope,note}:
  .github/workflows/auto-release.yml,project,Quote blocker issue search queries explicitly
tests[1]{command,scope,timeout_seconds,note}:
  test $(rg -c 'existing=.*--search.*search_query' .github/workflows/auto-release.yml) -eq 2,project,60,Both blocker lookup paths pass the named search query variable
